<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#990000"><b>What else to read</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Gerald Nicosia's <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FHome-War-History-Veterans-Movement%2Fdp%2FB000F4LO92%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1190157400%26sr%3D1-1&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">Home to War: A History of the Vietnam Veterans' Movement</a></i> is a history based on hundreds of interviews with men who fought in Vietnam and then came home to be active in the antiwar movement. <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FWar-Within-Americas-Battle-Vietnam%2Fdp%2F0595343961%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1190158023%26sr%3D1-2&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">The War Within: America's Battle Over Vietnam</a></i> by Tom Wells is a comprehensive history of the antiwar movement, from its earliest days to the end of the war in 1975.<p>
For an excellent history that focuses specifically on the GI rebellion during the war, read David Cortright's <i><a href="http://www.haymarketbooks.org/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=PROD&amp;Store_Code=Haymarket&amp;Product_Code=UHPSIR" target="_blank">Soldiers in Revolt</a>, </i>republished by Haymarket Books.<p>
<i>SW </i>columnist Paul D'Amato's article <a href="http://www.socialistworker.org/2005-1/545/545_06_Movement.shtml" target="_blank">"The Making of the Movement"</a> analyzes the earliest roots of the struggle to stop the Vietnam War.<p>
Joe Allen's <a href="http://www.isreview.org/issues/29/vietnam.shtml" target="_blank">three-part series on Vietnam</a> in the <i>International Socialist Review </i>provides a clear and accessible outline of the course of the war. The articles have been collected in a new book, <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FVietnam-Last-United-States-Lost%2Fdp%2F1931859493%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1190154318%26sr%3D1-1&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">Vietnam: The (Last) War the United States Lost</a></i>, due to be released later this year.
